A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Electronic Health Networks and Electronic Medical Record Vendors of Nursing
3 Homes – Release of Records – Enforcement
4 FOR the purpose of authorizing the Office of the Attorney General to enforce and certain
5 persons to bring a certain civil action regarding a certain provision of law authorizing
6 a nursing home that contracts with or uses an electronic health network or electronic
7 medical record vendor to direct the network or vendor to release electronic medical
8 records or electronic health care transactions to a business associate of the nursing
9 home; and generally relating to electronic health networks and electronic medical
10 record vendors of nursing homes.
11 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
12 Article – Health – General
13 Section 4–302.6
14 Annotated Code of Maryland
15 (2023 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
18 Article – Health – General
19 4–302.6.
20 (a) (1) In this section the following words have the meanings indicated.
21 (2) “Business associate” has the meaning stated in 45 C.F.R. § 160.103.
22 (3) “Electronic health care transactions” has the meaning stated in §
23 4–302.3 of this subtitle.
